In this op-ed article, First Lady Michelle Obama and Dr. Jill Biden discuss the importance of businesses hiring more veterans. They highlight the skills and training that veterans possess and the challenges they face in finding employment after their service. They mention the Joining Forces campaign, which aims to support veterans and military families, and the goal set by President Obama for the private sector to hire or train 100,000 veterans and military spouses by the end of 2013. They applaud the progress made so far, with businesses hiring or training 290,000 veterans and military spouses, but acknowledge that there is still work to be done. They call on businesses to commit to hiring veterans and provide opportunities for growth within their companies. They also mention efforts to extend tax credits for businesses hiring veterans and to revamp state laws to recognize the skills gained in the military. They emphasize the need for everyone to come together to support veterans and military spouses in finding meaningful employment.